We have denied the ultimatum by the <span style="color: #AF0202;">Left</span> faction, and expelled them from the party. They immediately move to form a new party, the <span style="color: #9B0000;">Socialist Workers' Party of Germany</span>, or the <span style="color: #9B0000;">**SAPD**</span>. A large portion of our union elements, as well as prominent <span style="color: #CE2D2D;">Centrist Marxists</span> members have followed the <span style="color: #AF0202;">Left</span>. Paul Levi has been chosen as it's interim leader. We will see what will come of this in future months. 

For now, we must lick our wounds, and search for our new direction. What will become of this new <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>?
